         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">TECHNOLOGICAL MUSEUM, SYDNEY. ¶ Memo. from the CURATOR to ¶  Baron von Mueller K.C.M.G., FRS ¶ 19th Sept:  ¶ 18 ¶ 92 ¶ Dear Baron Mueller, ¶  ¶ By this post I send sketch-drawing of  ¶ Hakea Bakeriana...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">92.09.19</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Maiden</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M14, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Grevillea macleayana</seg> (MEL 98862). MS annotation by M: 'Answ 22/9/92'. Letter not found. There is a file copy of this letter in the Library, Royal Botanic Gardens, Sydney.</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">TECHNOLOGICAL MUSEUM, SYDNEY.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">
                  <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Memo. from the CURATOR to</seg>
               </seg> Baron von Mueller K.C.M.G., FRS</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">19th Sept: <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">18</seg>92</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>By this post I send sketch-drawing of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Hakea%20Bakeriana">Hakea Bakeriana</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg>, which can be properly finished after you have examined it and made alterations (if any).<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The finished illustration by R. T. Baker accompanying B93.14.03, is plate 30 in the volume; the description cites plate 29, but that is an illustration of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Acacia maideni</seg>i, described in B93.09.06, where the description cites plate 28.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The matter of a species-name for the Grevillea might stand over for a little if you are agreeable.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See J. Maiden to M, 14 September 1892, and J. Maiden to M, 21 September 1892 (in this edition as 92-09-21a).</p>
               </note> Perhaps if it were called after my Minister<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">F. B. Suttor.</p>
               </note> it might be misunderstood; he might think I wished to curry favour. He is, all the same, a very good man, and bears an honoured name.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">F. Suttor was a grandson of George Suttor, one of the first botanical collectors sent by Joseph Banks to NSW.</p>
               </note> It might be more desirable to give it some name descriptive of the species.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I found it on flat, moist, sandy, barren land 2 or 3 miles as the crow flies from Jervis Bay and at no great elevation, say 100 feet, above the sea. I should require to define the place more accurately by means of a map, as it was not near a township or prominent landmark.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The species may require to be described (at least provisionally) in absence of fruits. It is 11½ miles from a main road &amp; in very rough country. I took a buggy &amp; nearly had a smash. The place is uninhabited &amp; it maybe a long time before I am able to revisit the locality.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">No species of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Grevillea</seg> named jointly by M and Maiden has been found. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours truly,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. H. Maiden.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I did look for fruits in July, but none were to be seen then.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Hakea%20Bakeriana">Hakea Bakeriana</name>
            </p>
         </div>
